features: 8-in-1 ATX power supply tester: Support testing 20-pin IDE/24-pin IDE/HDD/floppy disk 4-pin/PCI-e 6-pin/4-pin/8-pin/SATA connector.
Aluminum alloy shell: light and easy to carry, high strength, good thermal conductivity and corrosion resistance.

1.8" LCD screen: The output voltage is displayed on the 1.8" LCD screen, which is easy to read (1.8" LCD screen is powered by the 20-pin/24-pin connector). Note: Is there a scratch on the product screen? Because the screen is easy to scratch, we put a protective film on it, if you think it is not beautiful, you can tear it off by yourself.
Buzzer alarm: When your power supply PG number fails, the power tester will emit a buzzer alarm, which is easy to know.
When testing with HDD/floppy disk 4-pin/PCI-e 6-pin/4-pin/8-pin/SATA connector, the indicator on the left shows the output voltage (+12V + 3.3V + 5V).
body.description: Method of operation: 1. Insert the power supply 20PIN or 24PIN and P4, P6 or P8 into the corresponding position of the power supply tester. (If you insert a 20PIN or 24PIN interface tester alarm and display LL, you need to insert 4P! Please check 4P must be inserted into 4P position!) 2. Turn on the power, and the sound of "drip irrigation" sounds two kinds of sounds. If the value of each group does not flash, it means that the power input is normal. 3. If the circuit voltage signal is not detected (such as 20PIN or 24PIN connector) or the detected voltage exceeds the normal range, the buzzer will issue a "drip" warning for a long time, and the corresponding voltage or PG value will be displayed . If the status flashes, it means that the power supply is faulty! Support 20-pin/24-pin ATX power connector Support Molex/Xeco HDD power connector Support floppy drive power connector Support PCI-e 6-pin graphics card power connector Support P4 8-pin/4-pin CPU power connector Support SATA power connector (note: 4-wire SATA connector test + 3.3V light is not on, only 5-wire SATA connector can send SMS + 3.3V voltage) The package includes: 1x computer pc power supply tester
